{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Review an example project which provides a C\/C++ interface for macOS applications","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/release-notes","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/add-to-xcode","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/activating-license","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/discovering-connecting","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/device-operations","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/handling-measurements","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/faq","doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/example-apps"],"title":"Getting Started","generated":true,"anchor":"Getting-Started"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/wrapper"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"NixUniversalSDK"}],"title":"Wrapper for Usage in C\/C++"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For macOS applications that require a C\/C++ interface, it may be possible to use NixUniversalSDK indirectly. For example, the SDK download provides a project ","type":"text"},{"code":"example-macos-wrapper","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" which allows for its usage in C\/C++ applications.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This project contains single ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/IDeviceScanner","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.nixsensor.universalsdk\/documentation\/NixUniversalSDK\/IDeviceCompat","isActive":true},{"text":" instances. It provides a static interface to access these instances and also provides callbacks for device and scanner events. The project contains a basic implementation, but can be modified or expanded to better suit your specific application.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The wrapper project is part of the SDK examples which are available "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/www.nixsensor.com\/sdk-ios","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Building the wrapper project","anchor":"Building-the-wrapper-project"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is recommended to build the wrapper from the terminal using the provided build script. This script depends on the ‘Command Line Tools for Xcode’, which are available from the Apple Developer "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/download\/all\/"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open a terminal and navigate to the "},{"code":"example-macos-wrapper","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" folder"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Run the "},{"code":"build.sh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" script. The script takes an option:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"-c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Clean build folder","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"-d","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Build wrapper for debug","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-r"},{"type":"text","text":": Build wrapper for release"}]}]}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, to build the wrapper for release:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["sh build.sh -r"],"syntax":"shell","type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The build outputs will be located at the relative path ","type":"text"},{"code":"build\/Release","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (for a release build). These include:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"libNixUniversalSDK-Wrapper.dylib","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": wrapper library file with exported functions"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NixUniversalSDK-Wrapper.h"},{"text":": C\/C++ header file corresponding to the .dylib file","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"NixUniversalSDK.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": base "},{"code":"NixUniversalSDK","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" framework, required at runtime by "},{"code":"libNixUniversalSDK-Wrapper.dylib","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"start":3,"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Runtime requirements","type":"heading","anchor":"Runtime-requirements","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When using the wrapper library in a project, you must manually load the ","type":"text"},{"code":"NixUniversalSDK.framework","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" dependency at runtime (using ","type":"text"},{"code":"dlopen","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", for example). This framework must be loaded prior to calling the wrapper functions in ","type":"text"},{"code":"libNixUniversalSDK-Wrapper.dylib","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"NSBluetoothAlwaysUsageDescription","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"NSBluetoothPeripheralUsageDescription","type":